Topic (HelpDesk Support Requested Management):

- In organizations, technical support requests are frequently generated and must be carefully tracked to ensure timely resolution. A helpdesk system helps manage requests, assign tasks, and monitor work progress.

Required Functions:

- Create support requests with content, priority level, and submission time.
- Manage requester and support staff information.
- Assign support requests to staff members.
- Track request status: newly created, in progress, completed.
- Update processing progress and maintain a history of status changes.
- Search support requests by status or by requester.
